该算法首先假设元素集合中存在一个具有较低元素索引的元素，该索引被称为"中间"。然后，每个元素都被比较与中间元素，以确定最小和最大元素。

下面是一个基于Timsort的实现：
```lean
fun timsort(xs : seq[int]) : seq[int] {
  var i = 0
  var j = xs.len - 1
  while i < j {
    if xs[i] < xs[j] {
      swap(xs, i, j)
      i += 1
    } else {
      j -= 1
    }
  }
  if i == j { return xs }
  swap(xs, i, j) // swap the two largest elements at the end of the list to the beginning of the list. This is a critical step in Timsort.  This ensures that the largest elements are always together at the end of the list. Without this step, Timsort can sometimes fail to find all of the largest elements in a list. For example, if the list has three elements [1,2,3] and [2,3], then without this step, Timsort could fail to find the third element because it would assume that it was already sorted and did not look any further. But with this step, Timsort will find all of the largest elements because they are always together at the end of the list. This is an important detail to remember when using Timsort.
}
```
